{
  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "Expanded platform content moderation duties under the DSA Article 14 may conflict with GDPR data minimization requirements (Article 5), if applied excessively.",
    "There is also a risk of tension regarding compliance burdens, as meeting DSA's additional transparency and reporting obligations could create challenges for simultaneously meeting GDPR's data protection impact assessment and breach notification requirements.",
    "Ongoing coordination between national DPAs and the European Board for Digital Services (DSA Article 47) will help reconcile such potential tensions, ensuring cohesive interpretation and mutually reinforcing accountability aims while safeguarding innovation.",
    "• The Digital Markets Act (DMA) [59] entered into force in 2022 alongside the DSA.",
    "It aims to ensure fair competition and contestability for core platform services such as search engines, social networks, and marketplaces."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "• The Digital Markets Act (DMA) [59] entered into force in 2022 alongside the DSA."
  ]
}